originalText: ::The body bag in front of you contains a male corpse. The label on the bag reads: "Patrick Pierce." It appears that the corpse has been here for some time, but the extremely low temperature of the freezer prevented it from decaying.::

::You thoroughly examine the body. Visual inspections shows no signs of external injuries, bruises or similar. Opening the body cavity shows nothing out of the ordinary either, at least nothing that could indicate the cause of death. The skull was already opened earlier, but the brain doesn't seem to have been completely taken out of the skull during the previous autopsy. Once you remove it, however, you notice a small rupture of the brain's frontal lobe.::
